# Using BASH terminal to upload to Git hub
1. Open Your Project in VS Code
Make sure you have your personal-ai-data-agent folder open in VS Code.
2. Open the Terminal
Go to Terminal → New Terminal at the bottom.
3. Run These Commands One by One
Copy and paste one line at a time, then press Enter after each:
Bash
# 1. Make sure you're in the right folder
cd "C:\Path\To\your\personal-ai-data-agent"   # ← Change this if needed
# 2. Initialize Git (if not already done)
git init
# 3. Name the main branch
git branch -M main
# 4. Connect to your GitHub repo
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/personal-ai-data-agent.git
# 5. Add all your files
git add .
# 6. Commit your Day 1 work
git commit -m "Day 1: Complete setup with hello_world.py and folder structure"
# 7. Push to GitHub (this is the important one)
git push -u origin main --force
# The --force flag will replace everything currently on GitHub with your local version. This is what you asked for (“clean out my GitHub folder”).
